<section id="fs-id1359973" class="key-concepts">
<title>Key Concepts</title>
<list id="fs-id1482807" list-type="bulleted" bullet-style="bullet"><item><emphasis>Simple interest</emphasis>
<list id="eip-id1166402038051"><item>If an amount of money, <m:math><m:mi>P</m:mi></m:math>, the principal, is invested for a period of <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:math> years at an annual interest rate <m:math><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:math>, the amount of interest, <m:math><m:mi>I</m:mi></m:math>, earned is  <m:math><m:mi>I</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>P</m:mi><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:math></item>
<item>Interest earned according to this formula is called <term>simple interest</term>.</item></list></item>

</list></section>
